data.text:
Sveaskog will only process the personal data you provide to us, e.g. if you fill in your e-mail address, Sveaskog will process this personal data. Despite that, note that if you provide information in the message field that can identify you or any other person, that personal data will also be processed. You can choose to remain anonymous by not filling in personal information in the message box or by not typing in your email address. The purpose of our personal data processing is to improve our website by processing your feedback. Our legal basis for this purpose of the processing of your personal data is your consent, if you choose to fill in your personal data. Your personal data is processed until we process your feedback, and then we will delete your personal data.

Sveaskog will share your personal data with our technical solution provider. We do not transfer your personal data outside the EU/EEA.

When consent is the legal basis for the processing of your personal data, you have the right to withdraw such consent at any time. You have the right to request access to and further information about the processing of your personal data, or request that we correct, supplement, delete or restrict the processing of your personal data. You have the right to receive a copy of the personal data that we process about you free of charge once (1) a year. If you wish to request additional copies, we may charge a reasonable fee based on the administrative costs.

To exercise your rights or if you have questions about our processing of your personal data, please contact us at the following address: legal@sveaskog.se or call +46 771 787 000. Please provide your full name and please note that you may need to verify your identity before your request is processed.

If you have any complaints regarding our processing of your personal data, you can submit a complaint to the Swedish Authority for Privacy Protection via the following link: https://www.imy.se/en/individuals/forms-and-e-services/file-a-gdpr-complaint/
